          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cr was deposited electrolytically on Au(10micron) foils",
                "with thickness of 10 - 20 mg/cm2. Chemical purity was",
                "checked by atomic absorption spectrometry (97+-3%)",
                "25 samples were prepared",
                "100 and 250 micron thick Al and 20 micron Ti foils were",
                "used as monitor and energy degrader foils supplied by",
                "Goodfellow. (Purity 99.9%)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "STTA",
                "GSPEC",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "excitation function was measured via the",
                "activation technique using stacked foil targets.",
                "several stacks, each containing 1 electroplated Cr",
                "sample and some Ti foils were irradiated for 1-5 min",
                "at low 50-300 Na beam of He-3 particles.",
                "the beam current was determined using faraday cup as",
                "well as via the nat-Ti(He-3,x)V-48 monitor reaction.",
                "the two values were in 5 % agreement. Al foils were",
                "used to decrease the primary beam energy. The energy",
                "degradation was calculated according to williamson",
                "et Al. (Tables of range and stopping power of chemical",
                "elements for charged particles of energy 0.5 To 500 MeV",
                ",rapport CEA-R-3042 1966). Chemical separation was",
                "applied to measure the short lived Fe-52-m isotope.",
                "the usual gamma-spectrometry was applied to measure the",
                "radioactivity.",
                "nuclear data were taken from E. Browne,R.B.Firestone,",
                "Table of radioactive isotopes, ed. V.S.Shirley,",
                "Wiley, 1986, New York."
              ]
            }
          ],
